data.name: High-Protein Shrimp and Vegetable Soup
data.quickTastyDescription: A hearty, flavorful soup packed with protein from shrimp and a variety of colorful vegetables, slow-cooked to perfection.
detailedCookingInstructions: Heat olive oil in a large slow cooker on medium heat.
Add the chopped onion and minced garlic, saut√© for about 5 minutes until fragrant.
Stir in the diced carrots, celery, bell peppers, and zucchini; cook for another 5 minutes.
Pour in the vegetable broth and diced tomatoes; add the bay leaf, salt, and pepper.
Add the shrimp, stirring gently to combine, and cover the slow cooker.
Cook on low for 4 hours or until the vegetables are tender and the shrimp are cooked through.
Adjust seasoning to taste, remove the bay leaf, and serve hot, garnished with fresh parsley.
data.detailedName: Slow-Cooked High-Protein Shrimp and Vegetable Soup
